"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515743","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-27","<p>Between 2011 and 2016, we invested £860 million in a National Cyber Security Programme to deliver the 2011 UK Cyber Security Strategy. I made a Written Ministerial Statement on the 14<sup>th</sup> April to the House: “Final annual report on the 2011 – 2016 UK Cyber Security Strategy” with an accompanying Annual Report. Key achievements include the launch of the UK’s Computer Emergency Response Team; disruption of cyber threats by the new National Cyber Crime Unit and the growth of the Cyber Essentials scheme for companies. This year, we will be publishing a new five year strategy and launching a new National Cyber Security Centre in the autumn.</p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2016-04-27T11:24:52.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515743/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515743/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515743/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-21","Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what progress has been made on enhancing cyber-security in the UK.","false","Biography information for Graham Evans","Weaver Vale","Graham Evans","904714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516012","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-27","<p>The cost of the pamphlet and the website will have been just over £9 million.</p><p> </p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2016-04-27T15:23:30.12Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516012/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516012/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516012/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-21","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the cost to the public purse has been of all activity related to promoting the Government's policy of remaining in the EU, including staff costs and the writing and publishing of documents and web pages; and what estimate he has made of the total of such projected expenditure by the date of the EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Sir Bernard Jenkin","Harwich and North Essex","Mr Bernard Jenkin","904722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516013","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-27","<p>In central London, of 181 offices in 2010, only 54 remain. Rationalisation continues, enabling more multi-departmental use of HQ buildings and civil servants to move to peripheries where property costs are lower.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-27T14:43:31.53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516013/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516013/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516013/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-21","Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans he has to move policy-making civil servants out of London and into the regions.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","904724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516014","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-27","<p>In 2014-15, Central Government spent over £12 billion (27.1%) with small and medium sized businesses, which shows a continued year on year increase in SMEs winning public procurements.</p><p>The Government is determined to deliver its new target of one third of spend with SMEs by the end of this Parliament. The Crown Commercial Service is working with departments to develop and implement individual plans to deliver in 2020.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-27T14:44:44.35Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516014/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516014/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516014/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-21","Small Businesses: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans he has to ensure that his Department works with other government departments to increase procurement from small and medium-sized businesses.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","904725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516015","Cabinet Office","false","2016-04-27","<p>In 2014-15, Central Government spent over £12 billion (27.1%) with small and medium sized businesses, which shows a continued year on year increase in SMEs winning public procurements.</p><p>The Government is determined to deliver its new target of one third of spend with SMEs by the end of this Parliament. The Crown Commercial Service is working with departments to develop and implement individual plans to deliver in 2020.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-04-27T14:44:16.357Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516015/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516015/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/516015/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-04-21","Small Businesses: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to help SMEs win public procurement projects.","false","Biography information for Neil Carmichael","Stroud","Neil Carmichael","904721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514297","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-05-04","<p>We pay close attention to the human rights situation in China. We were concerned by reports that Ding Cuimei was buried alive on 14 April while protesting at the demolition of a church in Henan Province. We intend to raise Ding’s case at the next round of the annual UK-China Human Rights Dialogue.</p><p>We are aware of reports of the closure or demolition of churches and that individuals are being harassed or detained for their beliefs. We are aware, too, of reports of the recent disappearance of a number of Catholic priests in Hebei Province, such as Father Yang Jianwei. We are concerned by all instances where the whereabouts of detainees remains undisclosed, and where detainees are held without access to legal counsel or visits from relatives.</p><p>We continue to raise the full range of our concerns about freedom of religion and the restrictions placed on Christianity with the Chinese authorities. We also place on record our concerns in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office’s Annual Report on Human Rights and Democracy, published on 21 April, and in updates to it.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-05-04T12:56:34.827Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514297/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514297/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514297/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-04-20","China: Christianity","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of China about (1) reports of a pastor’s wife who was buried alive during the demolition of a church in Henan Province; (2) the demolition of churches, and the imprisonment and detention of religious leaders; and (3) the disappearance of several Catholic priests in Hebei Province.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL7787"
